text: Why did the scarecrow accept the job offer? Because it was outstanding in its field.
What do you call a dinosaur that can print in 3D? A Printasaurus Rex!
Why was the timeline so productive? Because it was always ahead of its time!
What's the difference between a pirate and a corporate raider? One says "Arrr!" and the other says "Shares!"
What's a pirate's favorite piece of artillery? The arrrrrr-m cannon!
I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.
Why was the PlayStation always picked first in gym class? Because it had the best controller!
Why did the division problem look so confused? Because it didn't know if it should feel divided or just remain remainder.
Why did the software developer go broke? Because he used up all his cache installing expensive programs!
Why don't secrets ever get sold at auctions? Because as soon as you bid on them, they're no longer priceless.
I went to an auction where they were selling a broken barometer. It was a no-pressure situation.
What did the crown say to the scepter? "You complete me!"
Why did the photon break up with the electron? It was tired of being in a relationship with so much negativity.
How do you organize a space party? You planet with Star Wars action figures!
You know you're mature when you attend a candle party and you're excited it's not because there's a blackout.
Why was the computer so proud of itself? Because it just downloaded a self-esteem booster pack!
Why did the vampire invest in acquisitions? He was looking for some new blood in the business!
I bought a plot in a cemetery, but that's the last thing I need.
Why doesn't Spencer play hide and seek with his friends? Because good Spencers are hard to find!
What do you call a dinosaur toy that never stops talking? A Dino-blabber!
Why was the heart a terrible gossip? It couldn't keep anything to itself and always spilled the blood.
Why did the Spanish pepper put on a sweater? Because it was a little chili.
I broke up with my timeline. It was too clingy, always talking about what we did at 3:02 PM last Tuesday.
Did you hear about the mathematician who's afraid of negative numbers? He'll stop at nothing to avoid them.
Why did the silk scarf break up with the wool sweater? It was tired of being in such a clingy relationship.
What's a ghost's favorite trick? A boo-lean operation!
What did the fundamental particle say at the bar? "I'll have a quantum of your finest energy, please. And keep the change!"
Why did the big company go on a shopping spree? Because it heard acquisitions were on sale вЂ“ buy one, get one free!
I asked my therapist how to deal with my obsession with vengeance. He said, "Let's not get even; let's get odd."
Why don't you ever see puzzles in the wild? Because they always end up in pieces at home!
Why don't people play hide and seek in Milan? Because good luck hiding when everyone's dressed to stand out!
Why did Spencer break up with his calendar girlfriend? He felt she was dating too many days at once!
Why don't possibilities ever get lonely? Because there's always potential for more!
What's a printer's favorite meal? Spaghetti with a side of paper clips вЂ“ it's the perfect feed!
Why did the tomato turn red? Because it saw the salad dressing and felt a little lower on the garden hierarchy.
Why did Spencer bring a ladder to the bar? He heard the drinks were on the house!
What did the vampire say to the mirror? "I can't see what's wrong with me."
What's Spencer's favorite exercise? Running late.
Why did the recycling bin break up with the trash can? It got tired of dealing with someone else's waste all the time!
Why don't secrets stay secret when you tell them to silk? Because it always lets things slip.
I asked the elevator why it was so good at its job. It said, "I've really taken things to a lower level."
How does Katie make her computer so smart? She gives it a daily dose of "Katie-bytes"!
I received an invitation to a claustrophobic's convention, but I'm not going. I heard the space is pretty tight.
What did Jose say when he won the lottery? "No way, Jose!"
Why was the fundamental particle always calm? Because it knew that in every situation, it could just quantum leap away.
Why did the gamer break up with his PlayStation? Because it was too possessive; it kept saying "This is for players only."
Why did the comedian get kicked out of the auction? Because every time someone made a bid, he said, "I'll throw in my two cents," and it just didn't add up.
How do you know when a merger is secretive? Even the pens they sign the deal with are under non-disclosure agreements!
I accepted that I'll never be good at origami, but that's okay. It's a fold I'm willing to leave unturned.
You know you're mature when your back goes out more than you do.
I tried to play hide and seek with my silk scarf, but it was sheer madness; it could never blend in!
Why did the computer get sick after downloading all those files? It caught a virus, now it's in bed with a bad case of data congestion.
Why did the cat come up with a scheme? To get the purr-fect opportunity to nap all day.
I told my friend I updated my camera's firmware. He said, "Wow, that's really exciting!" I could tell he was being sarcastic, or maybe he just needed an empathy firmware upgrade.
At what age is it appropriate to tell my dog that he's adopted? I think he's mature enough; he's already 42 in dog years.
Why did Jose refuse to play hide and seek? Because good luck hiding when everyone keeps shouting "Jose, can you see?"
I asked the artist if he could restore my old painting. He said he could, but it would cost me an "arm and a leg." I guess that's why the Mona Lisa is just a portrait.
Why was the possibility afraid of commitment? Because it didn't want to become a probability!
Why don't secrets work in a bank? Because there are too many tellers!
Why did the plot refuse to start at the beginning? It didn't want to be too predictable.
Why don't crowns use paper? Because they always rule the lines!
Why did the computer get a virus after installing new software? Because it didn't believe in antivirus shots.
Why did the bullet end up losing his job? Because he got fired!
Why was the bell so good at boxing? Because it knew exactly when to strike!
What do you call a crown that's a comedian? The "ruler" of punchlines!
Why did the crown go to school? Because it wanted to improve its "reign" of knowledge!
Why did the soccer team go to Milan? Because they heard there was a great "goal" of fashion there, and they wanted to score some style points!
What do you call Spencer when he's holding a map? Lost.
I told my friend she should embrace her mistakes. She gave me a hug immediately.
Why did the computer go to therapy? Because it had trouble accepting cookies!
Why did the smartphone go to therapy? It had issues with its firmware and couldn't process its own feelings.
I told my friend I had a job crushing cans. It was soda pressing, causing a real flattening in my career.
Why was the timeline so calm during the chaos? Because it knew everything would eventually fall into place.
What's a PlayStation's favorite snack? Microchips and dip.
Why did the broken computer take a nap? It needed to restore its energy!
How do printers apologize? They ream-orsefully admit their mistakes and promise better margins in the future.
What's a sea turtle's favorite kind of photo? A shellfie on the reef!
Why was the division symbol so popular at the party? Because it could really break the ice.
Why couldn't the bicycle stand up by itself? It was two-tired.
Why did the division sign apply for a job? It wanted to be the one splitting things up at the office.
Why was the tile comedian a hit at parties? Because its jokes were always flooring.
Why did the fundamental particle go to school? To improve its field of knowledge and become a force to be reckoned with!
I downloaded an app that tells me where to find the best seafood. It's a real net gain.
I tried to organize a strike at the calendar factory. Unfortunately, they said my days were numbered.
Why was the printer always upset? Because it kept jamming, even though it wasn't in a band!
I asked my boss how our company's latest acquisition was going. He said, "It's like marrying into a family with too many relatives вЂ“ suddenly you have more problems than you can count!"
Why don't mathematicians argue about division? Because it's pointless; they know they'll just end up going in circles.
I told my friend I was strikingly good at lightning photography. He said, "That's a flash in the pan."
Why did the math book look so sad? Because it had too many problems to lower its spirits.
How do you catch a unique possibility? Unique up on it! How do you catch a tame possibility? The tame way!
How do you throw a party for fundamental particles? You start with a big bang and let the forces do the rest!
Why did the mature computer go to therapy? Because it couldn't deal with its mid-life crisisвЂ”it had too many bytes of life left!
Firmware updates are like digital vegetables for your devices. They might not be fun, but they keep your system healthy!
Why did the computer break up with the printer? Because the printer had too many issues and the relationship was always paper-thin.
Why don't printers ever win at sports? Because they always seem to lose their paper chase!
Why did the clock get in trouble at work? Because it always struck at the wrong time!
Why don't old video games ever feel down? Because they can always be restored from a previous save point!
Why did the vampire become a computer technician? He was great at data recovery and restoring "byte."
What do you call a cat walking down the runway in Milan? A fash-purr-nista.
Why did the belt get arrested? Because it held up a pair of pants!
